{
  "stem": "8527.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was grateful for them, but I was afraid of them, because they were constantly demeaning me and-- and threatening me and telling me what a terrible thing I did to come there, to-- to cause them that kind of problem.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She didn't have the heart, apparently, to chase us out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Plus the fact there's another problem.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If she chased me out and if the Germans caught me, and if they beat me, I would probably tell them who hid me.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that-- that was a-- and that's what she threatened me with.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That's what she constantly said to us, my sister and I, if the Germans catch you, you're going to say who helped you, and they're going to kill us.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was a dichotomy of things.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She wanted to help us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She wanted to get rid of us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She couldn't get rid of us, you know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I used to go crazy there, just sitting around, killing lice.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I used to make designs.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I used to pee on the floor, you know, walking around.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One time he was going down to church.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I got carried away and peed right on his head.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] That didn't make any friends or influence people, but I remember doing those crazy things.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I remember being able to scream and holler and sing or cry when it was raining, because otherwise I couldn't make any noise.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When it was raining, the pounding of the rain on the tin roof was so dramatic, it was so loud, that it drowned out anything that I did.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Constantly hungry, wondering what would it be like to eat enough of food where you're able to say, I'm full.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
